post_text:
The purpose of my post this evening is to let you know that Mansfield Township School District will be observing the original spring break that has been in our calendar all school year starting Friday, April 10th. We will reopen for virtual learning on Monday, April 20th.

Food service will be suspended during the break and teachers and other educators will not be available for virtual learning.

I hope that you enjoy your break and we look forward to serving you again starting April 20th.

A parent update will be sent tomorrow, Thursday, April 9th and posted on our website with important information regarding our return on April 20th.

Have a great night!

Tiffany J. Moutis
Superintendent

post_text:
MTSD Community,

Though there are no confirmed COVID 19 cases in the MTSD family, to be proactive.......As of 3pm today, MTSD will be closed for two weeks. I will re-evaluate the situation on April 3rd.

The buildings will be checked daily. No staff or students will be allowed to enter the buildings.

All MTSD Staff will be working remotely and available to answer any emails you might send.

I hope you and your families are doing well and staying healthy!

Tiffany J. Moutis
Superintendent
